net.sourceforge.waters.model.module

Interface SimpleExpressionProxy

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ExpressionProxy, Proxy
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    BinaryExpressionProxy, EnumSetExpressionProxy, FunctionCallExpressionProxy, IdentifierProxy, IndexedIdentifierProxy, IntConstantProxy, QualifiedIdentifierProxy, SimpleIdentifierProxy, UnaryExpressionProxy
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BinaryExpressionElement, EnumSetExpressionElement, FunctionCallExpressionElement, IdentifierElement, IndexedIdentifierElement, IntConstantElement, QualifiedIdentifierElement, SimpleExpressionElement, SimpleIdentifierElement, UnaryExpressionElement

    public interface SimpleExpressionProxy
extends ExpressionProxy
    The base class of all expressions. This is the base class of all expressions that have a simple textual representation, i.e., one that easily fits into a single line. This includes all expressions except event lists (EventListExpressionProxy).
    Author:
    Robi Malik

      • getPlainText

        String getPlainText()
        Gets the original text of this expression. If present, this string contains the original text entered by the user, including all redundant parentheses and whitespace exactly as it was typed.
        Returns:
        The original text, or null to indicate that no original text is available.
